 T004: Control plane client\n33: - [ ] Create `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/__init__.py`\n34: - [ ] Create `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n35: - [ ] Implement `ControlPlaneClient.__init__(workload_manager_url, auth_token=None)`:\n36:   - [ ] Resolve URL from arg or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` env var\n37:   - [ ] Resolve token from arg or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`\n38:   - [ ] Create `requests.Session` with connection pooling\n39:   - [ ] Set `Authorization: Bearer {token}` header if token present\n40: - [ ] Implement `create_session(name, namespace, metadata=None, ttl=3600) -> str`:\n41:   - [ ] POST to `/v1/code-interpreter` with JSON `{name, namespace, ttl, metadata}`\n42:   - [ ] Return `data[\"sessionId\"]` or raise `ValueError`\n43: - [ ] Implement `delete_session(session_id) -> bool`:\n44:   - [ ] DELETE to `/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}`\n45:   - [ ] Return `True` on 404 or success, `False` on other errors\n46: \n47: ### T005: Code Interpreter data plane client\n48: - [ ] Create `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n49: - [ ] Implement `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.__init__(router_url, namespace, cr_name, session_id, timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0)`:\n50:   - [ ] Build base URL using `urljoin`\n51:   - [ ] Create `requests.Session`\n52:   - [ ] Set default header `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n53: - [ ] Implement `_request(method, path, **kwargs)`:\n54:   - [ ] Add timeout tuple `(connect_timeout, read_timeout)`\n55:   - [ ] Raise on HTTP errors\n56: - [ ] Implement `execute_command(command, timeout=None) -> dict`:\n57:   - [ ] POST to `api/execute` with JSON `{command: [...], timeout: \"<n>s\"}`\n58:   - [ ] Raise `CommandExecutionError` if `exit_code != 0`\n59: - [ ] Implement `write_file(path, content, mode=\"0644\")`:\n60:   - [ ] POST to `api/files` with base64-encoded content\n61: - [ ] Implement `upload_file(local_path, remote_path)`:\n62:   - [ ] Multipart POST